CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 7, 1958, pg. 1, reads: " Map Register - Vote Plans - Following their smashing victory in May 20 primary election, which saw their forces carry the regular endorsed Democratic ticket, headed by Mayor David L. Lawrence and Gov. George M. Leader, to victory, the Fifth Ward leadership, headed by Ward Chairman Robert E. (Pappy) Williams, met last weekend and made plans for a big Register-and-Vote Campaign... The drive got under way Tuesday. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Robert E. "Pappy" Williams lighting cigarette, Constable Thomas J. "Tommy" Smith, Alderman Harry Fitzgerald holding drink, Councilman Paul F. Jones, and K. Leroy Irvis seated on right, gathered in interior with display case with labeled figurines for voter registration meeting
